{"type":"text","timestamp":1778987890297,"sessionID":"ses_1cc16f0e6ffekDdP0f8Ru75kV9","part":{"id":"prt_e33f0de8a001naVArg9D7y7vU3","messageID":"msg_e33f0c606001O4x5q2Re5WBUOZ","sessionID":"ses_1cc16f0e6ffekDdP0f8Ru75kV9","type":"text","text":"The receptor pattern precedent is clear: receptor MF children usually carry a ligand-specific `has_part` binding term. Since `double-stranded RNA binding` already exists but there is no `left-handed Z-RNA binding`, I’m checking the ID range and preparing a minimal set of new terms that stays consistent with existing immune receptor curation.","time":{"start":1778987884170,"end":1778987890294}}}
